report.title: Chronological table of the titles of all the acts of parliament passed in the reign of King William III

section.head: CHRONOLOGICAL TABLE OF THE TITLES OF ALL THE ACTS OF PARLIAMENT PASSED IN THE REIGN OF KING WILLIAM III.

tr.td: DATE
TITLE or DESCRIPTION of the ACT.
NUMBER
Page of this Volume.
A.D.
Reign.
IN CHANCERY.
of the Chapter as printed.
On the Roll in Chancery.
Of the Original Act in Parliament.
W. III. An. 7, 8.
An Act for remedying the ill State of the Coin of the Kingdome.
I.

An Act for enlargeing the Times to come [in1] and purchase certain Annuities therein mentioned and for continuing the Duties formerly charged on Low Wines or Spirits of the first Extraction for carrying on the Warr against France.
II.
An Act for regulateing of Tryals in Cases of Treason and Misprision of Treason.
III.
An Act for preventing Charge and Expence in Elections of Members to serve in P[ar]liament.
IV.
An Act for granting to His Majesty an Aid of Four Shillings in the Pound(2) for carrying on the War against France.
V.
An Act for the more easie Recoverie of Small Tythes.
VI.
An Act to prevent False and Double Returns of Members to serve in Parliament.
VII.
An Act for the taking examining and stating the Publick Accounts.
VIII.
An Act for repairing the Highways betweene the City of London and the Towne of Harwich in the County of Essex.
IX.
An Act for continuing several Duties granted by former Acts upon Wine and Vinegar and upon Tobacco and East India Goods and other Merchandize imported for carrying on the Warr against France.
X.
An Act for impowering His Majestie to apprehend and detain such p[er]sons as hee shall find Cause to suspect are conspiring against His Royal Person or Government.
XI.
An Act for Relief of poor Prisoners for Debt or Damages.
XII.
An Act for taking off the Obligation and Incouragement for coining Guineas for a certaine Time therein mentioned.
XIII.
An Act for making navigable the Rivers of Wye and Lugg in the County of Hereford.
XIV.
An Act for the continueing meeting and sitting of a Parliament in case of the Death or Demise of His Majesty His Heirs and Successors.
XV.
An Act for raiseing the Militia of this Kingdom for the Year One thousand six hundred ninety six although the Months Pay formerly advanced bee not repaid.
XVI.
An Act to continue Foure former Acts for preventing Theft and Rapine upon the Northerne Borders of England.
XVII.
An Act for granting to His Majesty severall Rates or Duties upon Houses for making good the Deficiency of the clipped Money.
XVIII.
An Act to incourage the bringing Plate into the Mint to be coined and for the further remedying the ill State of the Coine of the Kingdome.
XIX.
An Act for granting to His Majesty an additionall Duty upon all French Goods and Merchandize.
XX.
An Act for the Increase and Encouragement of Seamen.
XXI.
An Act for preventing Frauds and regulating Abuses in the Plantation Trade.
XXII.

An Act for continueing severall former Acts for punishing Officers and Soldiers who shall mutiny or desert His Majesties Service and for punishing false Musters and for Payment of Quarters for One Yeare longer.
XXIII.
An Act requireing the Practicers of Law to take the Oaths and subscribe the Declaration therein mentioned.
XXIV.
An Act for the further regulating Elections of Members to serve in Parliament and for the preventing irregular Proceedings of Sheriffs and other Officers in the electing and returning such Members.
XXV.
An Act for repaireing the High-wayes betweene Wymondham and Attleborough in the County of Norfolk.
XXVI.
An Act for the better Security of His Maj[es]ties. Royal Person and Government.
XXVII.
p.6.I
An Act for the more effc[i]ual preventing the Exportac[i]on of Wooll and for [the3] incouraging the Importation there of from Ireland.
XXVIII.
An Act for the better amending & repairing the High-ways and Explanacion of the Laws relateing thereunto.
XXIX.

An Act for laying several Duties upon Low Wines or Spirits of the first Extraction and for preventing the Frauds and Abuses of Brewers Distillers and other Persons chargeable with the Duties of Excise
XXX.
p.7.I

An Act for continuing to His Majesty certaine Duties upon Salt Glass Wares Stone and Earthen Wares and for granting several Duties upon Tobacco Pipes and other Earthen Wares for carrying on the Warr against France and for establishing a National Land Bank and for taking off the Duties upon Tunnage of Shipps and upon Coals.
XXXI.
p.8.I
An Act for the Ease of Jurors and better regulating of Juries.
XXXII.
p.9.I
An Act for the better Incouragement of the Greenland Trade.
XXXIII.
An Act that the Solemne Affirmation & Declaration of the People called Quakers shall be accepted instead of an Oath in the usu´l Forme.
XXXIV.
An Act for the inforcing the Laws which restraine Marriages without Licence or Banns & for the better registring Marriags Births and Burials.
XXXV.
An Act for continuing several Acts of Parliam[en]t. therein mentioned.
XXXVI.
An Act for the Encouragem[en]t of Charitable Gifts and Dispositions.
XXXVII.
An Act to take away the Custome of Wales which hinders persons from disposeing their Personal Estates by their Wills.
XXXVIII.
An Act for encourageing the Linen Manufacture of Ireland and bringing Flax and Hemp into and the making of Sail Cloth in this Kingdome.
XXXIX.

(4) An Act for revesting in His Majesty the Honor of Tutbury Forrest of Needwood severall Mannors Parkes Lands and Offices and other Profitts thereunto belonging: and for vacatting certein Letters Patents therein mentioned.
XL.

tr.th: THE TITLES OF THE PRIVATE ACTS.

tr.td: An Act for enableing the Lady Katherine Fane to sell the Reversion of certaine Fee-Farme Rents given her by her Grandfather John Bence Esq[uire].
i.

An Act for enableing Sir Thomas Parkyns Baronett to sell certain Messuages Lands and Hereditaments in Huby and Easing Would in the County of York and the settling other Lands & Hereditaments of greater Value in lieu thereof.
ii.
An Act to enable Sir Thomas Pope Blount Baronett to make a Settlement upon the Marriage of his eldest Son.
iii.
An Act for vesting the Manor of Madley in the County of Salop in Trustees for certaine Purposes therein mencioed.
iv.
An Act for the enableing Thomas Stoner Esq Son and Heire of John Stoner Esquire deceased to make a Jointure and Settlement of his Estate in Marriage not withstanding his Minority.
v.
An Act for vesting several Messuages and Lands belonging to Samuel Powell Esquire in Trustees for Payment of his Debts.
vi.
An Act to enable Anthony Earle of Kent and Henry Grey his Son and Heire Apparent make a Jointure for to Jemina Wife of the said Henry Grey.
vii.
An Act to enable the Lord Francis Powlett to charge his Estate with Provisions for his younger Children.
viii.

An Act for vesting the Estate late of Sir Nicholas Stoughton and Sir Lawrence Stoughton Baronetts deceased in Trustees to be sold for the Payment of their Debts and raiseing Portions for the Daughters of the said Sir Nicholas Stoughton.
ix.
An Act to enable Richard Haynes Esquire to settle a Joynture on his now Wife and to exchange Lands with the Trustees of Thomas Stevens Esquire deceased.
x.
An Act for enableing Trustees to sell Part of the Estate of Edmond Warner deceased for Payment of his Debts and for preserving the rest for the benefitt of his Heire.
xi.
An Act to enable John Aunger an Infant and his Mother to make a Lease of his Estate for the Improvement thereof.
xii.

An Act to enable Trustees to sell Part of the Manor of Barkhampstead and to pay of the Incumbrances charged on the same and to lay out the Overplus in an Estate to be settled as the said Manor is now vested.
xiii.
An Act for naturalizing Henry de Nassau and other Children of Henry de Nassau Seignior de Auverquerke.
xiv.
An Act to enable John Fownes Esquire to sell certaine Lands in the County of Devon which were settled on his Marriage and to settle other Lands of an equal Value to the same Uses.
xv.

An Act to enable Trustees to exchange Lands of Sir James Chamberlaine Baronett an Infant lying in the Common Hill or Feild of Salford in the County of Oxford for like Quantities of Lands there in order to the making an Inclosure.
xvi.

An Act to enable the Parish of St. James within the Liberty of the City of Westminster to raise upon themselves so much Money as will discharge their Debt for building their Parish Church Rectors House Vestry and other Publick Works there.
xvii.

An Act to ascertaine and settle the Payment of the Impropriate Tythes of the Parish of St. Lawrence Old Jury in London to the Master and Scholars of Balliol College in Oxford and for confirming an Award made concerning the same.
xviii.
An Act for naturalizeing James Stanhope Esquire and others.
xix.
An Act for naturalizing Salomon Eyme & others.
xx.

An Act to confirme & establish an Exchange made between Thomas Rider Esquire and Christopher Clitherow Esq[uire] of certaine Messuages in London for the Manors of Bilsington and other Lands in Kent of the like Value.
xxi.

An Act to enable Trustees to fill upp Leases of the respective Estates of Bluet Wallop Esq[uire] and John Wallop Gent? dureing theire Minorities and to purchase other Lands by the Fines thereby to be received to the same Uses as the Estates so to be leased are already settled.
xxii.

An Act for enabling Trustees to sell the Mannor of Pespoole in the County of Durham Part of the Estate of William Midford an Infant for Payment of Debts and Incumbrances charged thereon and for preserving the rest of the said Infants Estate.
xxiii.

An Act for impowering the most Noble Anne Dutchesse of Buccluch and the Right Honorable James Earle of Dalkeith her Son of the Kingdome of Scotland to grant Leases for improving a Peece of Ground in the Parish of Saint Martins in the Fields in the County of Middlesex.
xxiv.
An Act to enable Trustees to raise Money for the making a Wett Dock and improving the Estate of the Marquesse and Marchionesse of Tavistock att Rodderith in the County of Surrey.
xxv.
An Act to naturalize William commonly called Viscount Tunbridge and other Children of the Earle of Rochford.
xxvi.
An Act for the better Improvement of a House and Ground in Great Queen Street.
xxvii.

An Act to enable Trustees to sell a Messuage Garden and Outhouse in Lincolnes-Inn Fields late Sir Robert Sawyers Knight deceased and for purchasing other Lands and Tenements to be settled to the same Uses.
xxviii.

An Act for settling divers Lands and Rent-Charge on the Rector of the Church of Maydwell in the County of Northampton and his Successors and in lieu thereof for settling other Lands and dischargeing Tythes belonging to the said Church according to several Agreements between the Patron and the said Rector made upon the incloseing of Lands in Maydwell and afterwards with the Consent of the Ordinary confirmed by several Decrees in the Court of Chancery.
xxix.
An Act for settling the Personal Estate of Richard Jones Esquire and Mary Gufford Spinster [Minors5] in Trustees for the Purposes therein mentioned.
xxx.
An Act for the better supplying the City of Bristoll with Fresh-Water.
xxxi.
An Act for erecting of Hospitals and Work-houses within the City of Bristoll for the better imploying and maintaining the Poor thereof.
xxxii.
An Act for making good the last Will of Sir. William Barkham Baronett deceased and vesting of Lands in Trustees to be sold for Payment of his Debts and making Provision for his Children.
xxxiii.
An Act to enable Sir Charles Heron Baronett to sell Lands for Payment of a Portion and Debts.
xxxiv.
An Act to enable Sir Thomas Wagstaffe Knight to raise & secure a Portion for Frances his onely Daughter and Heire Apparent.
xxxv.

An Act for vesting the Moiety of the Manor of Shipton Mallett in the County of Somersett and divided Moiety of the Manor of Wells in the said County in Trustees to be sold for Payment of a Mortgage charged thereon and for making a Provision for the Maintenance of Mary the Wife of William Sandes Esq[uire] and her Children.
xxxvi.
An Act for makeing the Townes of Stretton and Princethorpe a separate Parish from Wolston in the County of Warwick.
xxxvii.
An Act for vesting Part of the Estate of Joseph Dawson Esq[uire] in Trustees for Payment of Debts and for a Provision for the Maintenance and Marriage of his Daughters.
xxxviii.

An Act for Sale of Lands in Horsington in the County of Somersett Part of the Estate of William Ridout an Infant for Payment of Incumbrances charged thereon and for preserving the Residue of the said Estate for the Infant.
xxxix.
An Act for vesting certaine Lands of Thomas Bigg and his Wife in Chislett in the County of Kent in Trustees for Payment of Debts and making Provision for their Children.
xxxx.

An Act for revesting in His Majesty the Honor of Tutbury Forrest of Needwood several Manors Parks Lands and Offices and other Profitts thereunto belonging and for Vacating certains Letters Patents therein menc[i]oed.
xxxxi.
An Act for importing and coining Guineas and Halfe-guineas.
I.
p. I.I
An Act for the further remedying the ill State of the Coin of the Kingdome.
II.

An Act to explain that Part of the Act passed last Session of Parliament for laying several Duties on Low Wines & Spirits of the first Extraction and for preventing the Frauds and Abuses of Brewers Distillers and other Persons chargeable with the Duties of Excise which relates to the Payment of Tallies & the Interest thereof.
III.
An Act to attaint Sir John Fenwick Baronett of High Treason.
IV.

An Act to attaint such of the Persons concerned in the late horrid Conspiracy to assassinate His Majesties Royal Person who are fled from Justice unlesse they render themselves to Justice and for continuing several others of the said Conspirators in Custody.
V.
An Act for granting an Aid to His Majesty as well by a Land Tax as by several Subsidies and other Duties payable for One Yeare.
VI.
An Act for granting to His Majesty several Duties upon Paper Vellum and Parchment to encourage the bringing of Plate and hammered Money into the Mints to be coined.
VII.
An Act for incouraging the bringing in wrought Plate to be coined.
VIII.
An Act to restore the Markett att Blackwell-Hall to the Clothiers & for regulating the Factors there.
IX.
An Act to enable the Returns of Juries as formerly until the First Day of November One thousand six hundred ninety seven.
X.
An Act for the better preventing frivolous and vexatious Suits.
XI.
An Act for continuing several additional Impositions upon several Goods and Merchandizes.
XII.

An Act for continuing several former Acts for punishing Officers and Soldiers who shall mutiny or desert His Majesties Service and for punishing false Musters and for Payment of Quarters for One Yeare longer.
XIII.
An Act for the compleating the building and adorning the Cathedral Church of Saint Paul London & for repaireing the Collegiate Church of Saint Peter Westm?.
XIV.
An Act for (6) repairing the Highway betweene Ryegate in the County of Surrey & Crawley in the County of Sussex.
XV.
An Act for enlargeing Co[m]mon High-ways.
XVI.
An Act for paving and regulating the Hay-Markett in the pish of Saint Martin in the Fields and Saint James within the Liberty of Westminster.
XVII.
p. 4. not numbered on the Roll.
An Act for Relief of Creditors by making Composition with their Debtors in Case Two Thirds in Number & Value doe agree.
XVIII.
An Act for repealing a Clause in a former Act relateing to Party Guiles and for the better preventing Frauds and Abuses [in7] Brewers and others chargeable with the Duties of Excise.
XIX.
An Act for making good the Deficiencies of several Funds therein mentioned and for enlargeing the Capital Stock of the Bank of England and for raising the Publick Creditt.
XX.

An Act for laying a Duty upon Leather for the Terme of Three Yeares and making other Provision for answering the Deficiences as well of the late Duties upon Coals & Culme as for paying the Anumities upon the Lottery and for Lives charged on the Tūnage of Ships and the Duties upon Salt.
XXI.

An Act for granting to His Majesty certain Duties upon Malt Mum Sweets Cyder & Perry as well towards carrying on the Warr against France as for the necessary Occasions of His Maj[es]ties Household & other Occasions.
XXII.
An Act to enforce the Act for the Encrease and Encouragement of Seamen.
XXIII.

An Act for granting to His Majesty a further Subsidy of Tunnage and Poundage upon Merchandizes imported for the Terme of Two Yeares & Three Quarters & an additional Land Tax for One Yeare for carrying on the Warr against France.
XXIV.
An Act for licensing Hawkers and Pedlars for a further p[ro]vision for the Payment of the Interest of the Transport Debt for the reducing of Ireland.
XXV.
An Act for the better p[re]venting the counterfeiting the current Coine of this Kingdome.
XXVI.
An Act for the more effectual Relief of Creditors in Cases of Escapes & for preventing Abuses in Prisons and pretended priveledged Places.
XXVII.
An Act for the better Observation of the Course anciently used in the Receipt of Exchequer.
XXVIII.
An Act for the Repaire of the Peers of Bridlington alies Burlington in the East-Riding of the County of York.
XXIX.
An Act for supplying some Defects in the Laws for the Relief of the Poor of this Kingdom.
XXX.
An Act for the easier obtaining Partitions of Lands in Coparcenary Joynt Tenancy & Tenancy in Common.
XXXI.
An Act to restraine the Number and ill Practice of Brokers and Stock-Jobbers.
XXXII.
p. II. 1
An Act to make p[re]petual and more effectual an Act intituled An Act to prevent Delays att the Quarter Sessions of the Peace.
XXXIII.
An Act for the lessening the Duty upon Tin and Pewter exported and granting an Equivalent for the same by a Duty upon Druggs.
XXXIV.
An Act for raiseing the Militia for the Yeare One thousand six hundred ninety seven although the Months Pay formerly advanced be not repaid.
XXXV.
An Act for the further Encouragement of the Manufacture of Lustrings and Alamodes within this Realme and for the better preventing the Importation of the same.
XXXVI.

An Act for explaining and enforcing the Act for paving and cleansing the Streets within the Cities of London and Westminster and Borough of Southwark & weekly Bills of Mortality and Streets adjoyning thereunto & for widening the Street at the South end of London-Bridge.
XXXVII.
An Act for naturalizing Frederick Christiaen de Rhede commonly called Lord Aghram and others.

An Act for the Settlement of the Mannor of Treyagoe in the County of Hereford and other the Lands late of Crompton Mynors Esquire deceased and for raising and encreasing of the Portion of Theodosia Mynors the Daughter of the said Crompton she being an Infant of the Age of Seventeene Yeares.
ij.

An Act for vesting the Manor of Holme alias East Holme and Swannage in the County of Dorsett part of the Estate of Sir John Hotham Baronett in Trustees to be sold for discharging a Mortgage thereupon and upon the residue of the said Sir John Hothams Estate & for Payment of his other Debts.
iij.
An Act for enabling Oliver Neve of Great Witchingham in the County of Norffolk Esquire to sell Two Houses in London and for vesting other Lands in the said County of greater Value to the same Uses.
iiij.

An Act for enabling James Duke of Ormond to raise Money by Sale of Woods and making Leases for Lives renewable for ever for Payment of Debts and for encourageing English Plantation in Ireland and for Charles Lord Weston Earle of Arran in the Kingdome of Ireland to make Leases of his Estate in the said Kingdome.
v.
An Act for the Exchange of certaine Advowsons betweene the Bishopp of London and the Earle of Nottingham.
vj.
An Act for the speedy satisfying the Debts of Francis late Lord Holles deceased.
vij.
An Act to enable Sir Ralph Ashton Baronett to supply an omission of Limitation intended in his Marriage Settlement for the Benefitt of his Issue Male.
viij.
An Act for the Sale of the Estate of Francis Griffith late of London Scrivener deceased for Payment of his Debts.
ix.
An Act for settling the Estate of Mary Savile an Infant upon her Marriage.
x.
An Act to enable the Sale of Lands late of Jeoffery Stockley in the County of Chester deceased for Payment of his Debts and for making Provision for Mary his Daughter.
xj.

An Act for vesting certaine Messuages Lands and Tenements late of Charles Milson deceased in Trustees to sell for Payment of Debts and Legacies and lay out the Surplus Money in a Purchase of Lands for the Use of Edward Milson and his Heires according to the Will of the said Charles Milson.
xij.

An Act to enable Nicholas Goodwin the elder and Nicholas Goodwin the younger to sell the Mannor of Winslow in the County of Bucks and with the Moneys ariseing thereby and other Moneys to be advanced by the said Nicholas Goodwin the elder to purchase Lands of a greater yearely Value to be settled to the same Uses as the said Manor is now settled.
xiij.
An Act for the vesting of certaine Lands of William Melward in the County of Hereford Clerk in Trustees for Payment of Debts.
xiiij.

An Act for vesting the Estate of Edward Kerrey Esquire lying in Binoeston in the County of Salop in Trustees to discharge Incumbrances thereon and to raise Portions for younger Children and for confirming the Marriage Settlement of the said Edward Kerrey.
xv.
An Act for vesting Part of the Estate of Thomas Panton Esquire in Trustees to be sold for Payment of Debts and securing a Jointure to Mary his now Wife.
xvj.
An Act for naturalizing John Keyser & others.
xvij.

An Act to enable Edward Leigh Esquire and Jane his Wife and their Trustees to sell the Mannors of Waxham and Horsey and certaine Lands and Tenements in the County of Norffolk and to purchase and settle other Lands to the same Uses.
xviij.
An Act for vesting and settling certaine Estates of William James Gent in and upon Trustees to be sold for the Payment of Debts & making Provision for himselfe his Wife and their Children.
xix.
An Act for importing several Goods and Merchandizes laden in Turkey on board the Shipps called the Successe and Draggon Galley paying Customes as if imported by English Shipps.
xx.
An Act to enable William Fallows an Infant to sell an Estate in the County of Chester to pay Debts secured by Mortgages.
xxj.
An Act to supply a Defect in an Act for enabling Oliver Neve Esquire to sell Two Houses in London and for settling Lands in the County of Norffolk of greater Value to the same Uses.
xxij.

An Act explaining a former Act of Parliament intituled An Act for enabling Trustees to sell Part of the Estate of Edmund Warner deceased for Payment of his Debts and for preserving the rest for the Benefitt of his Heires.
xxiij.

An Act for vesting Part of the Estate of Roger Crowle Esquire deceased in Trustees for raiseing Portions for his Younger Children in regard hee (being a Lunatick) could not execute a Power in his Marriage Settlement for that Purpose.
xxiiij.

An Act to vest certaine Lands late of Samuel Trotman Esquire deceased lying in Barking Eastham Westham and Woolwich in the Counties of Kent and Essex in Trustees to be sold and to settle other Lands in lieu thereof.
xxv.
An Act for the speedy Payment of the Debts of Sir William Thompson Knight Serjeant att Law deceased.
xxvj.
An Act for annulling the Marriage of Hannah Knight an Infant and directing the Guardianshipp of the said Infant.
xxvij.

An Act for the enabling the Sale of the Mannor of Rowling in Kent which by Mistake was by General Words comprized in the Marriage Settlement of the said William Hamond Gent contrary to the Meaning of the Parties.
xxviij.
An. 9.
An Act against corresponding with the late King James and his Adherents.
I.
p.1. I

An Act to prevent the further Currency of any hammered Silver Coine of this Kingdome & for recoining such as is now in being and for the making out new Exchequer Bills where the former Bills are or shall be filled upp by Indorsements.
II.
An Act to give further Time for the administring of Oaths relating to Talleys & Orders and for the easier Dispatch of the Publick. Businesse in the Exchequer & in the Bank of England.
III.
An Act for continuing the Imprisonment of Counter and others for the late horrid Conspiracy to assassinate the person of His Sacred Majesty.
IV.

An Act for satisfying and discharging the Arreares of several Annuities which incurred betweene the Seventeenth Day of May One thousand six hundred ninety six and the Seventeenth Day of May One thousand six hundred ninety seven.
V.
An Act that all Retailers of Salt shall sell by Weight.
VI.
An Act to prevent the throwing or firing of Squibbs Serpent? & other Fire-works.
VII.
An Act for explaineing an Act made the last Session of Parliament for granting to His Majesty certaine Duties upon Malt Mum Sweets Cyder & Perry.
VIII.
An Act for rendring the Laws more effectual for preventing the Importation of Forreign Bone-Lace Loom-lace Needle-work Point & Cutt-work.
IX.

An Act for granting to His Majesty the Sum of One Million foure hundred eighty foure thousand & fifteene Pounds one Shilling eleaven Pence three Farthings for disbanding Forces paying Seamen and other Uses therein mencioed.
X.

An Act for explaining an Act made the last Session of Parliament entituled
An Act for supplying some Defects in the Laws for the Relief of the Poorof this Kingdome.
XI.
An Act for the inlargeing repaireing and preserving the Bridge & Key of the Borough of Bridgewater in the County of Somersett.
XII.
An Act for granting to His Majestie several Duties upon Coals and Culm.
XIII.
An Act for continuing the Duties upon Coffee Tea and Chocolate and Spicestoward? Satisfaction of the Debt due for Transport Service for the Reduction of Ireland.
XIV.
An Act for determining Differences by Arbitration.
XV.

An Act to execute Judgment? & Decrees saved in a Clause in an Act of the First Yeare of the Reigne of King William and Queen Mary intituled
An Act for taking away the Court holden before the President and Council of the Marches of Wales.
XVI.
An Act for the better Payment. of Inland Bills of Exchange.
XVII.
An Act for repairing the Highways from the Town of Birdlipp and the Top of Crickley Hill in the County of Gloucester to the City of Gloucester.
XVIII.
An Act for cleansing & making Navigable the Channel from the [Hithe8] att Colchester to Wivenhoe.
XIX.

An Act to naturalize the Children of such Officers and Souldiers & others the natural borne Subjects of this Realme who have been borne abroad during the Warr the Parents of such Children haveing been in the Service of this Government.
XX
An Act for the better preventing the counterfeiting clipping and other diminishing the Coine of this Kingdome.
XXI.

An Act to repeale an Act made in the Nine and thirtieth Yeare of the Reigne of Queen Elizabeth intituled (An Act to restraine the excessive making of Malt) and to discharge & vacate Orders made by Justices of Peace by virtue thereof for restraining Malsters from makeing Malt.
XXII.

An Act for granting to His Majesty a further Subsidy of Tunnage and Poundage towards raiseing the Yearly Summ of Seven hundred thousand Pounds for the Service of His Majesties. Household & other Uses therein mencioned dureing His Majesties Life.
XXIII.
An Act for inlarging the Time for purchasing certain Estates or Interests in several Annuities therein mentioned.
XXIV.
An Act for granting to His Majesty His Heires & Successors further Duties upon Stampt Vellum Parchment. & Paper.
XXV.
p.5.I
An Act to settle the Trade to Africa.
XXVI.
An Act for licensing Hawkers and Pedlars for a further Provision of Interest for the Transport Debt for reduceing of Ireland.
XXVII.
An Act for the exporting Watches Sword-hilts and other Manufactures of Silver.
XXVIII.
An Act to repeal the Act made the last Session of Parliament intituled An Act for Relief of Creditors by making Composition with their Debtors in case Two Thirds in Number and Value do agree.
XXIX.
An Act for increasing His Ma[jes]ties Duties upon Lustrings and Alamodes.
XXX.
An Act for raising the [Milita9] for the Year One thousand six hundred ninety eight although the Months Pay formerly advanced be not [paid.10]
XXXI.
(11) An Act for preventing Frauds and Abuses in the charging collecting & paying the Duties upon Marriages Births Burials Batchellors and Widowers.
XXXII.
(12) An Act for the Increase and Preservation of Timber in the New Forest in the County, of Southampton.
XXXIII.
(13) An Act for applying to the Use of His Majesties Navy and Ordnance the Overplus of the Money and Stores which were provided for the building Seven and twenty Ships of War.
XXXIV.
(14) An Act for the more effectual suppressing of Blasphemy and Profaneness.
XXXV.
(15) An Act to stop the coining Farthings and Halfpence for One Year.
XXXVI.
(16) An Act for the better and more orderly Payment of the Lottery Tickets now payable out of certain additional Duties of Excise and of other Annuities lately payable out of (17) Tunnage Duties.
XXXVII.
An Act for granting to His Majesty an Aid by a Quarterly Poll for One Year.
XXXVIII.
An Act for settling and adjusting the Proportion of Fine Silver (18) Silk for the better making of Silver and Gold Thread and to prevent the Abuses of (19) Wire-Drawers.
XXXIX.
An Act for the Explanation and better Execution of former Acts made against Transportation of Wool Fullers Earth and Scouring Clay.
XL.
An Act for the better preventing the Imbezlement of His Majesties Stores of War and preventing Cheats Frauds and Abuses in paying Seamens Wages.
XLI.
An Act for enlarging the Time for registring of Ships pursuant to the Act for preventing Frauds and regulating Abuses in the Plantation Trade.
XLII.
An Act for the better Incouragement of the Royal Lustring Company and the more effectual preventing the fraudulent Importation of Lustrings and Alamodes.
XLIII.
An Act for raising a Sum not exceeding Two Millions upon a Fund for Payment of Annuities after the Rate of Eight Pounds per Centum per Annum and for settling the Trade to the East Indies.
XLIV.

An Act for taking away Half the Duties imposed on Glass Wares and the whole Duties lately laid on Stone and Earthen Wares and Tobacco Pipes and for granting (in lieu thereof) new Duties upon Whale Fins and Scotch Linen.

An Act for naturalizing John Ricard Jacob Dabbadie and others.
An Act for naturalizing Francis Vandertyd, and Agneta Vandermersch Henry Lowman and James Gabriel Le Tresor.
An Act for naturalizing Isaac Delagard John Batero and others.
An Act for renewing the Bills of Credit commonly called Exchequer Bills.
I.
An Act for the further Limitation of the Crown and better securing the Rights and Liberties of the Subject.
II.
An Act for preventing any Inconveniencies that may happen by Priviledge of Parliament.
III.
An Act for appointing Wardens and Assay Masters for assaying Wrought Plate in the Cities of York Exeter Bristol Chester and Norwich.
IV.
An Act for continuing a former Act to prevent false and Double Returns of Members to serve in Parliament.
V.
An Act for continuing the Acts therein mentioned for preventing Theft and Rapine upon the Northern Borders of England.
VI.
An Act for the better settling and preserving the Library kept in the House at Westminster called Cotton House in the Name and Family of the Cottons for the Benefit of the Publick.
VII.
An Act for raising the Militia for One Year although the Months Pay formerly advanced be not repaid.
VIII.
An Act for the recovering secureing and keeping in repair the Harbour of Minehead for the Benefitt and Support of the Navigation and Trade of this Kingdom.
IX.

An Act for granting an Aid to His Majesty for defraying the Expence of His Navy Guards and Garrisons for One Year and for other necessary Occasions. Stated in the Long Calender to be on the top Press in the Parliament Office.
X.

An Act for granting to His Majesty several Duties upon Low Wines or Spirits of the First Extraction and continuing severall additional Duties upon Coffee Tea Chocolate Spices and Pictures and certain, Impositions upon Hawkers Pedlars and Petty Chapmen and the Duty of Fifteen per Cent. upon Muslins and for improving the Duties upon Japanned and Laquered Goods and for continuing the Coinage Duty for the several Terms and Purposes therein mentioned.
XI.

An Act for appropriating Three thousand seven hundred Pounds weekly out of certain Branches of Excise for publick Uses and for making a Provision for the Service of His Majesties Household and Family and other His necessary Occasions.
XII.
An Act to enable His Majesty to make Leases and Copies of Offices Lands and Hereditaments Parcel of His Dutchy of Cornwall or annexed to the same and for Confirmation of Leases already made.
XIII.
An Act for the more speedy Payment of the Creditors of James late Duke of Ormond and of the present Duke of Ormond.

An Act to enable the Right Honourable Elizabeth Viscountess Bulkeley of Cashells in the Kingdom of Ireland to sell certain Lands in the County of Devon and City and County of the City of Exon for the Payment of Debts.
ij.

An Act to enable Robert Lord Viscount Kilmorey of the Kingdom of Ireland (being an Infant) to settle divers Mannors [Lands46] and Hereditaments in the Kingdom of England upon a Treaty of Marriage. 1interlined on the Roll
iij.
An Act to enable Sir Charles Barrington Baronet to settle a Joynture and make Provision for his younger Children.
iiij.

An Act to enable Sir Robert Marsham Knight and Baronet to dispose of Lands in Hertfordshire and to settle other Lands of better Value in Kent to the same Uses as the Lands in Hertfordshire are settled.
v.
An Act for erecting Hospitals and Workhouses within the Borough of Kings Lynn in the County of Norfolke for the better imploying and maintaining the Poor there.
vj
An Act for erecting a Court of Request or Conscience in the City and County of the City of Norwich for the Recovery of small Debts under Forty Shillings.
vij.
An Act to enable Stephen Jermyn to make Provision for his younger Children and for the Advancement of his eldest Son.
viij.

An Act for the vesting and settling divers Mannors and Lands in South Pickenham and other Places in the County of Norfolke in Trustees to be sold and for laying out the Moneys ariseing by Sale thereof in the Purchase of other Lands to be settled to such and the same Uses as the said Mannors and Lands so to be vested are and stand settled.
ix.
An Act for discharging a Mortgage upon the Estate of Peter Trevisia Esquire deceased and providing a Maintenance for his Widow and Children.
x.
An Act for the more speedy Payment of the Debts of Christopher Killiow Esquire and for the raising Portions and Maintenance for his Brothers and Sisters in pursuance of his Fathers Will.
xj.
An Act for vesting the Estate of Humphrey Hide Esquire deceased in Trustees for raising Portions for his younger Children.
xij.
An Act for furnishing the Town of New Deal with Fresh Water.
xiij.

An Act for vesting a Messuage and Lands in Stevenage in the County of Hertford the Estate of Richard Nodes in Trustees to be sold for making a Provision for his Wife and Children equal to the Provision secured to them out of the said Estate.
xiv.
An Act for Sale of the Estate of William Davison Esquire deceased for Payment of Debts and raising his Childrens Portions charged thereupon.
xv.
An Act for separating James Earl of Anglesea from Katharine Countess of Anglesea his Wife for the Cruelty of the said Earl.
xvj.
An Act for dissolving the Marriage of Sir John Dillon with Mary Boyle and for other Purposes therein mentioned.
xvij.
An Act to dissolve the Marriage of Ralph Box with Elizabeth Eyre and to enable him to marry again.
xviij.
An Act for the vesting several Messuages Lands and Tenements belonging to John Fawconer Esquire in Trustees to be sold for Payment of Debts.
xix.
An Act for transferring a Trust in Lands belonging to the City of London unto new Trustees.
xx.
An Act for removing the County Goal of Hertford.
xxi.
An Act for the better Performance of the last Will of Henry Apsley Esquire deceased.
xxij.
An Act for vesting the Estate of Thomas Bennet late of Newton cum Barton in the County of Chester in Trustees for the Use of the Poor of Westkirby pursuant to the Will of the said Thomas Bennet.
xxiij.
An Act to enable William Vaughan Esqr and Frances Vaughan his intended Wife (being both under the Age of One and twenty Years) to perform Articles made for their Marriage.
xxiv.
An Act to change the Sirname of Ellis Mews and his Heirs to the Sirname Saint John.
xxv.
An Act for making [good46] the Deficiency of the Charges of making a Way out of Chancery Lane into Lincolns Inn Fields.
xxvj.

An Act for declaring the Will of Sir Joseph Herne Knight dated the Twenty fifth Day of February One thousand six hundred ninety eight to be taken and esteemed the last Will of the said Sir Joseph Herne.
xxvij.
An Act for naturalizing Jane Barkstead Widow and vesting several Mortgages and Securities in her to enable her to convey or assign the same.
xxviij.
An Act for naturalizing Archibald Arthur and enabling him to dispose of his Estate.
xxix.
An Act for naturalizing Jacob Auguste Pyngot and others.
xxx.
An Act for naturalizing Adrian Lofland and others.
xxxj.
An Act to enable Sir Thomas Stanley Bar[one]t to charge certain Mannors and Lands in the County of Lancaster with Three hundred Pounds for Payment of his Sisters Portions and his Debts.
xxxij.
An Act for the Sale of the Estate of James Deane and for securing the Moneys raised thereby for the Benefit of himself and Family according to the Settlement thereof.
xxxiij.
An Act to enable Richard Bigg to charge Part of his Estate in the County of Hertford and Bedford with the Payment of his Debts.
xxxiiij.
An Act for naturalizing Peter Bagneol Daniel Senault and others.
xxxv.
An Act for naturalizing Gasper Cordoso Herman Vant Wedde and others.
xxxvj.

An Act for reviving and continuing an Act intituled an Act for the appointing Commissioners to take examine and determine the Debts due to the Army Navy and for Transport Service and also an Account of Prizes taken during the late War.
I.
An Act for punishing Officers and Soldiers that shall mutiny or desert in England or Ireland.
II.
An Act for the Attainder of the pretended Prince of Wales of High Treason.
III.
An Act for continuing an Act intituled An Act that the solemn Affirmation and Declaration of the People called Quakers shall be accepted instead of an Oath in the usual Form.
IV.
An Act for granting an Aid to His Majesty by laying Duties upon Malt Mum Cyder and Perry.
V.

An Act for the further Security of His Majesties Person and the Succession of the Crown in the Protestant Line and for extinguishing the Hopes of the pretended Prince of Wales and all other Pretenders and their open and secret Abettors.
VI.
An Act to naturalize Charlotte the Wife of Hugh Boscowen Esquire.

An Act for enabling Lionel Earl of Orrery in the Kingdom of Ireland by Sale of certain Lands and Tenements to raise Money for Payment of his Debts and settle other Lands to the Uses and Purposes in this Act mentioned.
